    intro: "This body fat calculator is calibrated for women, using the U.S. Navy method with the additional hip circumference measurement that's essential for female body fat estimation. Women naturally carry more body fat than men — 10-13% essential fat (vs 2-5% for men) needed for reproductive health, hormonal balance, and overall wellbeing. Healthy body fat for women ranges from 20-30%, with athletic women at 14-20%. The Navy method accounts for female-specific fat distribution patterns (hips, thighs, breasts) and provides a more nuanced assessment than BMI, which can't distinguish between fat, muscle, bone, and water weight. Understanding your body fat percentage empowers you to set realistic fitness goals, track progress beyond the scale, and make informed decisions about nutrition and exercise.",
