    intro: "India's diverse but predominantly hot and humid climate makes proper hydration critically important — and most Indians don't drink enough water. With summer temperatures regularly exceeding 40-45°C across North India, Rajasthan, Central India, and the Deccan Plateau, water loss through sweat can be 2-3 liters per day during peak heat. Even in moderate seasons, the Indian lifestyle — spicy food, chai/coffee consumption, outdoor work, and intense cooking — increases fluid needs. This water intake calculator estimates your ideal daily water consumption based on your body weight and activity level, with specific adjustments for Indian climatic conditions. Whether you prefer plain water, coconut water (nariyal pani), buttermilk (chaas), lemon water (nimbu pani), or green tea — knowing your daily target is the first step to staying hydrated, energetic, and healthy.",
