    intro: "Congratulations, mommy-to-be! This pregnancy due date calculator is designed specifically for Indian women, providing your Expected Delivery Date (EDD) along with context relevant to the Indian healthcare system — from government hospital registration timelines to recommended prenatal tests at major Indian chains like Apollo, Fortis, and Manipal. Using Naegele's rule (the same method your OB-GYN uses), the calculator estimates your due date from your last menstrual period (LMP) and shows you a complete pregnancy timeline. In India, prenatal care is available through government hospitals (free under PMJAY/Ayushman Bharat), private hospitals, and nursing homes. Early registration (by 8-12 weeks) ensures you get regular checkups, timely scans, and a booked delivery slot. Whether this is your first pregnancy or your third, knowing your EDD helps you plan everything from maternity leave to baby shopping.",
